Had this at a party and had to get the recipe. Amazingly simple in ingredients and preparation, but huge on flavor. I agree with another reviewer, I sometimes crave this dish, especially in the summer. I've made it several times for guests to rave reviews, every time. I've also varied the nuts and cheeses. Yum!

Rating: 4
This is the first time I've reviewed a recipe, I must admit. Thank you to all of you who do it regularly- I appreciate it! I'll now add my two cents as I couldn't resist. This is AMAZING! The chicken does need to cook longer as it was raw in parts. I sauted in shallots & oil for a few mins to finish cooking and then combined w/the pan juices (minus some fat, plus a tsp soy). Dressing was perfect as is although added dill instead of thyme, which was great! Can't go wrong w/this recipe!! Used only 2 breasts, halved the dressing ingreds and enough for four.

