I've made this twice now for shower menus and each time it has earned rave reviews. Very simple ingredients but the textures (velvety chicken, crisp green beans) and flavorful dressing combine to make a truly memorable dish. I use haricots verts for a more sophisticated presentation, toast the walnuts, and use garlic olive oil for the dressing. Really really delicious.

Rating: 4
I have made this recipe several times since I first tried it back in 2001. It is delicious and -- in my opinion -- very unique. I love the idea of using green beans as a main ingredient in a salad. I wondered if the salad would be a little bland because the recipe has limited ingredients, but, instead, it is continually rich and interesting. It's also pretty quick to prepare, as well as healthy, so it's great summer dish.

