Rating: 2
This was good but not the best chicken salad recipe of its type. I believe this is mainly due to the method and ingredients for cooking the chicken. The marinade produced an oily and tasteless chicken, especially with cooking the chicken for so litle time. The chicken needed to be cooked at least another 15 minutes in the oven to be done. Also the dressing needed to be seasoned a bit more. I toasted the walnuts first to make the flavor come out.

Rating: 4
I made this as part of the menu for our annual St. Patrick's Day party, and everyone loved it. I cooked the chicken a bit longer than 20 minutes, as it wasn't quite done at that point. I think dried thyme would work as well as fresh, also.

Rating: 3
made this salad for a potluck -- it was delicious, and i got lots of compliments. the recipe is huge, and i cut it down to about 1/3 of the size somewhat successfully (the potluck was for 10 people). i gave it 3 rather than 4 forks only because it is slightly bland. if i make it again i might try using more herbs in the dressing and while baking the chicken. also, it's probably better made in the summer, as the original article suggests!

